01:40:47.900 --> 01:40:54.990
in terms of marginalizing people
sometimes violently attacking,

01:40:54.990 --> 01:40:59.060
so the right to atheism which
by the way is the majority

01:40:59.060 --> 01:41:03.880
of the population of France
is either agnostic or atheist,

01:41:03.880 --> 01:41:05.770
is not so respected in America

01:41:05.770 --> 01:41:09.370
because by definition America has
always been a religious country

01:41:09.370 --> 01:41:11.450
from the very beginning
of American history.

01:41:11.450 --> 01:41:14.720
So, what is your reaction
to this kind of opinion

01:41:14.720 --> 01:41:16.730
that I hear all the time?

01:41:16.730 --> 01:41:19.780
&gt;&gt; It's the law on the books and
the law in action, to be sure.

01:41:19.780 --> 01:41:23.190
We're very generous in respecting
the religious freedom of all

01:41:23.190 --> 01:41:25.850
but there are certain groups
that we constantly vilify,

01:41:25.850 --> 01:41:29.860
Native American Indians,
Scientologists, Wiccans,

01:41:29.860 --> 01:41:35.900
increasingly today Muslims,
intermittent episodes

01:41:35.900 --> 01:41:37.990
of anti-Semitism, anti-Judaism.

01:41:37.990 --> 01:41:40.850
We do have our laundry
list of social pariahs

01:41:40.850 --> 01:41:45.040
and sometimes the courts
are blind to their plight.

01:41:45.040 --> 01:41:49.800
I will say with respect to atheism,
the Supreme Court rather early

01:41:49.800 --> 01:41:54.190
in a case of 1961 called
Torcaso versus Watkins,

01:41:54.190 --> 01:41:59.500
upheld the free exercise
right of an atheist to refuse

01:41:59.500 --> 01:42:02.500
to swear an oath that educed God.

01:42:02.500 --> 01:42:06.680
He could give an alternative form
of demonstrating his veracity,

01:42:06.680 --> 01:42:09.380
the court concluded and
did so on the strength

01:42:09.380 --> 01:42:14.160
of the free exercise right of
that individual and the worry

01:42:14.160 --> 01:42:19.880
about establishing a theism from
which he would become a victim.

01:42:19.880 --> 01:42:25.540 position:56%
And so the court rather early was in
the vanguard really around the world

01:42:25.540 --> 01:42:28.000
in thinking of western
constitutional values

01:42:28.000 --> 01:42:32.200
of protecting atheism
but that's a hard sell

01:42:32.200 --> 01:42:35.070
when the Cold War logic
was very much

01:42:35.070 --> 01:42:38.030
about we are the great
Christian nation

01:42:38.030 --> 01:42:41.400
and those atheistic communists
out there are doing their thing

01:42:41.400 --> 01:42:47.600
and that case gets lost in the
ensuing decades of Cold War logic,

01:42:47.600 --> 01:42:54.580
but it's early for many
important signposts

01:42:54.580 --> 01:42:58.930
of a generosity towards people
of faith and of no faith

01:42:58.930 --> 01:43:02.630 position:56%
and the protection they should
enjoy under the free exercise clause

01:43:02.630 --> 01:43:07.360
and increasingly, I think in
the 21st century we've come

01:43:07.360 --> 01:43:10.500
to recognize demographically
that the nones

01:43:10.500 --> 01:43:13.910
on various religious demographics,
the nones are getting bigger

01:43:13.910 --> 01:43:18.010
and bigger especially in the
younger generation and their plight

01:43:18.010 --> 01:43:20.770
and the protection of their
plight, I think is going

01:43:20.770 --> 01:43:24.390
to be an important part of
our story going forward.

01:43:24.390 --> 01:43:30.890
The hard question I think, that
we have to face is whether atheism

01:43:30.890 --> 01:43:33.350
and none are the same thing.

01:43:33.350 --> 01:43:35.550
It's one thing to have
an affirmative belief

01:43:35.550 --> 01:43:38.790
in the non-existence of
God as an atheist has,

01:43:38.790 --> 01:43:41.760
it's another thing
simply to be abstaining

01:43:41.760 --> 01:43:46.650 position:56%
from any religious participation and
any religious involvement or ideas

01:43:46.650 --> 01:43:51.360
and the European Court
of Human Rights has,

01:43:51.360 --> 01:43:55.770
under the European Convention
Article IX, the notion of thought,

01:43:55.770 --> 01:43:58.860
conscience and belief and
it's a grab gab that allows

01:43:58.860 --> 01:44:04.030
for the religion of atheism
and the none to be combined

01:44:04.030 --> 01:44:07.800
in zealous protection for what
we would call religious freedom.

01:44:07.800 --> 01:44:11.440
We don't have that textual
luxury in the United States

01:44:11.440 --> 01:44:16.680
and we have religion and we are
jealous about protecting sincere,

01:44:16.680 --> 01:44:21.210 position:56%
good faith idiosyncratic, newly
acquired understandings of the faith

01:44:21.210 --> 01:44:24.000
but there is a presumption
of faith there

01:44:24.000 --> 01:44:28.540
and I think the hard question
becomes well, is the protection

01:44:28.540 --> 01:44:33.210
of religious freedom as
Jefferson himself said to Madison,

01:44:33.210 --> 01:44:35.410
is the protection of
religious freedom as soon

01:44:35.410 --> 01:44:40.740
as you establish one form of
faith, you automatically begin

01:44:40.740 --> 01:44:44.380
to disenfranchise those
of non-faith.

01:44:44.380 --> 01:44:47.080
And the analogous questions
now are beginning to emerge,

01:44:47.080 --> 01:44:49.790
does the protection of religious
freedom, the privileging of those

01:44:49.790 --> 01:44:54.800
who have faith inevitably begin to
compromise the status, the rights,

01:44:54.800 --> 01:44:58.990
the entitlements that those
who have no faith don't enjoy.

01:44:58.990 --> 01:45:00.920
Now, there's a couple
of answers to that.

01:45:00.920 --> 01:45:06.370
One is that free exercise of
religion rights are also balanced

01:45:06.370 --> 01:45:11.040 position:56%
by a no establishment guarantee that
says yes, there is free exercise

01:45:11.040 --> 01:45:13.390
of religion but you're going
to have to do it on your own.

01:45:13.390 --> 01:45:17.460
